timeline.bodyText:
This looks like it can/should be refactored to use try-with-resources:
try (DataInputStream dis = new DataInputStream(new FileInputStream(certPath))) {
// do stuff
}

This is assuming that these resources are autocloseable, but I would expect they are. Generally anything that is autocloseable should be wrapped in a try-with-resources, since it guarantees that the resource is properly closed, even if an exception is thrown or there is an early return statement or any other exit condition. Probably all of the various Streams in here should be wrapped in this way.

