replies.bodyText:
What "parsing errors"? Does it throw a CertificateException, and if so, does the exception say anything informative?
The official docs suggest that passing the FileInputStream wrapped in a BufferedInputStream should be sufficient: https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/security/cert/CertificateFactory.html
ie.
 FileInputStream fis = new FileInputStream(filename);
 BufferedInputStream bis = new BufferedInputStream(fis);

 CertificateFactory cf = CertificateFactory.getInstance("X.509");

 while (bis.available() > 0) {
    Certificate cert = cf.generateCertificate(bis);
    System.out.println(cert.toString());
 }

and
 FileInputStream fis = new FileInputStream(filename);
 CertificateFactory cf = CertificateFactory.getInstance("X.509");
 Collection c = cf.generateCertificates(fis);
 Iterator i = c.iterator();
 while (i.hasNext()) {
    Certificate cert = (Certificate)i.next();
    System.out.println(cert);
 }

It would be much better if we can figure a way to generate the certificate more directly from a stream of the file, without first reading the whole file into an application memory buffer and making a stream out of that. Less bug prone and probably better overall throughput performance.

